### Describe the bug

When creating a user profile with a birthday attribute which should be displayed with a date picker in the registration dialogue this input will always fail validation when using local-date-validation.



### Version

18.0.0

### Expected behavior

The user is created and has the attribute birthday set as iso 8601 date.



### Actual behavior

The birthday field is flagged as invalid.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5465291/165805491-ea75e524-ca4c-4fff-aa59-fd12e0d00657.png)

Another interesting sidenote: The date format in the date picker didn't change with a localization change.

In the form data I can see it being sent as:
```
birthday: 2022-01-01
```

### How to Reproduce?

In a realm with declarative user profile with the following configuration:

```
{
  "attributes": [
    {
      "name": "username",
      "displayName": "${username}",
      "validations": {
        "length": {
          "min": 3,
          "max": 255
        },
        "username-prohibited-characters": {}
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "email",
      "displayName": "${email}",
      "validations": {
        "email": {},
        "length": {
          "max": 255
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "selector": {
        "scopes": []
      },
      "permissions": {
        "view": [
          "user",
          "admin"
        ],
        "edit": [
          "user",
          "admin"
        ]
      },
      "name": "birthday",
      "displayName": "Birthday",
      "required": {
        "roles": [],
        "scopes": []
      },
      "validations": {
        "local-date": {}
      },
      "annotations": {
        "inputType": "html5-date"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Then try to register a new account.

